      "section_2_detailed": [
        "urban (/ˈɜː.bən/) [adj]: thuộc về thành thị, đô thị *e.g., Towns and cities are called urban areas.*",
        "suburban (/səˈbɜː.bən/) [adj]: thuộc về vùng ngoại ô *e.g., Holywood is a suburban town of Belfast.*",
        "rural (/ˈrʊə.rəl/) [adj]: thuộc về nông thôn *e.g., Further away, you reach rural areas — the countryside.*",
        "countryside (/ˈkʌn.tri.saɪd/) [noun]: vùng nông thôn, miền quê *e.g., Many people enjoy the peace of the countryside.*",
        "hamlets (/ˈhæm.lət/) [noun]: những làng nhỏ (thôn xã rất nhỏ) *e.g., In the countryside you find villages and hamlets.*",
        "settlements (/ˈset.l.mənt/) [noun]: khu định cư *e.g., Rural areas have smaller settlements than cities.*",
        "public transport (/ˈpʌb.lɪk ˈtræn.spɔːt/) [noun phrase]: phương tiện giao thông công cộng *e.g., Public transport is limited in the countryside.*",
        "open space (/ˈəʊ.pən speɪs/) [noun phrase]: khoảng không gian mở, đất trống *e.g., The countryside has more open space than the city.*",
        "cleaner air (/ˈkliː.nər eər/) [noun phrase]: không khí trong lành hơn *e.g., There is cleaner air in the countryside than in the city.*",
        "quiet environment (/ˈkwaɪ.ət ɪnˈvaɪ.rən.mənt/) [noun phrase]: môi trường yên tĩnh *e.g., The quiet environment helps people feel relaxed.*",
        "live in the suburbs (/lɪv ɪn ðə ˈsʌb.ɜːbz/) [phrase]: sống ở ngoại ô *e.g., People who live in Holywood live in the suburbs.*",
        "nightlife (/ˈnaɪt.laɪf/) [noun]: cuộc sống về đêm *e.g., Cities offer plenty of cinemas, restaurants, and nightlife.*",
        "crowds (/kraʊdz/) [noun]: đám đông *e.g., The noise, traffic, and crowds can increase stress in a city.*",
        "fast pace (/fɑːst peɪs/) [noun phrase]: nhịp độ nhanh *e.g., Some people find the fast pace of city life exhausting.*",
        "advantages and disadvantages (/ədˈvɑːn.tɪ.dʒɪz ənd dɪs.ədˈvɑːn.tɪ.dʒɪz/) [phrase]: thuận lợi và khó khăn, ưu và nhược điểm *e.g., Both ways of living have advantages and disadvantages.*",
        "distractions (/dɪˈstræk.ʃənz/) [noun]: những thứ gây xao nhãng *e.g., In a quiet village there are fewer distractions.*",
        "peaceful surroundings (/ˈpiːs.fəl səˈraʊn.dɪŋz/) [noun phrase]: môi trường yên bình *e.g., Good concentration often improves in peaceful surroundings.*",
        "convenience (/kənˈviː.ni.əns/) [noun]: sự tiện lợi *e.g., Some people choose city life for its convenience and excitement.*",
        "rural areas (/ˈrʊə.rəl ˈeə.ri.əz/) [topic_vocabulary]: các khu vực nông thôn *e.g., There are not so many jobs in rural areas.*",
        "city life (/ˈsɪt.i laɪf/) [topic_vocabulary]: cuộc sống thành thị *e.g., Cities offer more opportunities, but city life is not perfect.*"
      ]
